It's a flying saucer!
Come on, you got to see it!

01:56.050 --> 01:57.861
- It's great! Come on, everybody!
- POTSIE: Flying saucer?

01:57.885 --> 01:59.023
(Snaps fingers)

02:03.891 --> 02:05.402
(Snaps fingers)

02:05.426 --> 02:07.804
This never happened
to me before.

02:08.729 --> 02:09.872
(Snaps fingers)

02:09.896 --> 02:12.075
Yeah, Fonz?

02:12.099 --> 02:13.910
Oh... it's getting worse!

02:13.934 --> 02:16.413
Now I'm getting chubby men!

02:16.437 --> 02:19.582
Boy, I don't care
if he is our best friend,

02:19.606 --> 02:22.218
-he's cracking up!
-(laughter)

02:22.242 --> 02:23.920
What do you mean?
What's cracking up?

02:23.944 --> 02:25.655
Who's cracking up?
What's going on here?

02:25.679 --> 02:29.092
I think Richie's wah, wah, wah
has gone woo, woo, woo.

02:29.116 --> 02:31.027
(laughter)

02:31.051 --> 02:33.730
POTSIE:
Hey, Rich! Rich, tell Fonz.

02:33.754 --> 02:35.065
I dare you.

02:35.089 --> 02:37.333
- Yeah, yeah, tell him, nutso.
-(laughter)

02:37.357 --> 02:39.202
All right, hold it, stop.
That's enough.

02:39.226 --> 02:41.905
I don't want to hear nothing
about my buddy Richie.

02:41.929 --> 02:44.274
'Cause what he says,
you believe.

02:44.298 --> 02:47.510
You think that
this face right here lies?

02:47.534 --> 02:49.879
Fonz, I just saw
a flying saucer.

02:49.903 --> 02:51.915
Hey, what are you, nutso?

02:51.939 --> 02:54.551
- Did you see any
little green men? -(laughter)

02:54.575 --> 02:56.252
Look, look,
the man's obviously overtired.

02:56.276 --> 02:58.722
Too much studying.
You better get some sleep, Rich.

02:58.746 --> 03:01.691
I'm telling you,
I saw a flying saucer.

03:01.715 --> 03:03.426
Uh, Rich,
this happens all the time

03:03.450 --> 03:06.062
to people that
live humdrum lives.

03:06.086 --> 03:08.732
- Humdrum? -Yeah. When you
got nothing else going

03:08.756 --> 03:11.367
in your life, your brain
kind of exaggerates, you know?

03:11.391 --> 03:13.303
Now, wait a minute,
I'm not humdrum.

03:13.327 --> 03:16.172
I may be a little tired,
but I... I'm not humdrum.

03:16.196 --> 03:18.875
You're not humdrum, huh?
What do you do with your nights?

03:18.899 --> 03:21.111
All right, fine.
I-l come home,

03:21.135 --> 03:22.412
- I eat dinner...
- Yeah.

03:22.436 --> 03:23.680
- Do my homework...
- Yeah.

03:23.704 --> 03:25.048
Watch a little TV,

03:25.072 --> 03:26.783
uh, Friday nights
I play basketball,

03:26.807 --> 03:29.619
Saturday nights I go on a date,
Sunday nights I rest.

03:29.643 --> 03:31.987
OTHERS:
Humdrum!

