- Anybody home?
-(clicks on TV)

03:46.160 --> 03:49.004
(music, whooping,
guns firing on TV)

03:50.297 --> 03:52.876
"Richie, your father
made us go to the movies

03:52.900 --> 03:55.176
"before the prices change.

03:57.171 --> 04:00.550
"I left you a cold fish plate.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.787
Love, Mom."

04:03.811 --> 04:07.486
Ugh. Cold fish
and soggy French fries.

04:08.916 --> 04:10.918
(groans)

04:12.319 --> 04:13.930
Well, here I am...

04:13.954 --> 04:16.867
eating leftovers, watching TV.

04:18.492 --> 04:21.837
I don't know,
maybe I am humdrum.

04:25.232 --> 04:26.376
(knocking)

04:26.400 --> 04:28.107
Oh. Come in.

04:34.975 --> 04:37.320
(high-pitched voice
speaks alien language)

04:37.344 --> 04:38.788
Uh...

04:38.812 --> 04:40.256
hi, Ralph.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.325
Great Alvin the chipmunk
imitation.

04:42.349 --> 04:44.928
Now, come on in and sit down.
I'm trying to watch this show.

04:44.952 --> 04:47.796
(high-pitched voice
speaks alien language)

04:49.323 --> 04:51.166
(high-pitched):
Boop...!

04:53.160 --> 04:54.867
Good evening, earthling.

05:02.369 --> 05:04.347
You're not Ralph.

05:04.371 --> 05:06.516
(speaks alien language)

05:06.540 --> 05:09.719
Now, wait a minute,
a-are you...

05:09.743 --> 05:11.287
I was right! You're...

05:11.311 --> 05:13.523
Did you say... "earthling"?

05:13.547 --> 05:14.525
(speaks alien language)

05:15.549 --> 05:16.793
Are you an alien?

05:16.817 --> 05:18.628
-(high-pitched): Ah.
- All right, put 'em up!

05:18.652 --> 05:20.864
- Boop...!
- Yeah, right, cancel that.

05:20.888 --> 05:22.699
Right, now, just, uh...

05:22.723 --> 05:24.701
just-just take it easy,
all right?

05:24.725 --> 05:27.203
I mean, just-just stay...
very calm, because, uh...

05:27.227 --> 05:29.405
I come in peace.
No, no, you're the one.

05:29.429 --> 05:31.374
You-you come in peace. I...

05:31.398 --> 05:33.910
Look, will you just calm down?
Calm down for one second!

05:33.934 --> 05:37.447
Relax, earthling.
I mean you no harm.

05:37.471 --> 05:38.815
Oh.

05:38.839 --> 05:41.885
Sure. How am I supposed to know?

05:41.909 --> 05:44.888
(speaking alien language)

05:44.912 --> 05:49.359
What do you do, do you just, uh,
use that to scare people with?

05:49.383 --> 05:51.090
No, keeps rain off my head.

05:52.753 --> 05:55.298
Are you Richie Cunningham?

05:55.322 --> 05:57.700
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, th-that's me.

05:57.724 --> 06:00.270
- Is this your house?
- Uh-huh.

06:00.294 --> 06:02.296
Eh-eh, eh-eh.

06:04.598 --> 06:06.409
Wait a minute, who are you?

06:06.433 --> 06:09.107
I am Mork from Ork.
(speaks alien language)

06:10.671 --> 06:12.947
(speaks alien language)

06:17.144 --> 06:20.421
A-And those guys
said I was crazy.

06:21.448 --> 06:23.059
Hey, hey, I just...

06:23.083 --> 06:25.628
I... I got the best idea.
I want to show those guys, see?

06:25.652 --> 06:27.230
Will you come down
to Arnold's with me?

06:27.254 --> 06:29.766
-(speaks alien language)
- Oh.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.901
Right, right.

06:31.925 --> 06:34.737
Hey, if you're Mork from Ork...

06:34.761 --> 06:37.106
then I got
a tremendous scoop here!

06:37.130 --> 06:38.508
- Scoop?
- Uh, story.

06:38.532 --> 06:39.976
News story.
Uh, look, would you mind

06:40.000 --> 06:41.678
if I just ask you
a few questions?

06:41.702 --> 06:43.079
Fire away, bucko.

06:43.103 --> 06:45.515
Bucko. That's great.

06:45.539 --> 06:47.517
- Okay, would you just
mind having a seat? -Seat?

06:47.541 --> 06:49.953
- Yes.
-(speaking alien language)

06:57.684 --> 06:59.495
Mork, you...

06:59.519 --> 07:02.131
you know my nickname,
you know where I live--

07:02.155 --> 07:04.300
you don't even know how to sit?

07:04.324 --> 07:06.970
See, you just...
you put your, uh... down.

07:06.994 --> 07:08.838
Oh. (speaks alien language)

07:08.862 --> 07:12.342
-(beeping, whirring)
- Ah...

07:12.366 --> 07:14.243
Good.

07:14.267 --> 07:17.547
Okay, your name is, uh, Mork,

07:17.571 --> 07:20.216
and you come
from the planet Ork.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.720
Ever been to New York?
(chuckles)

07:25.479 --> 07:27.357
Just a little Earth humor.

07:27.381 --> 07:28.925
Oh, humor.

07:28.949 --> 07:30.760
(loudly):
Ah, ah!

07:30.784 --> 07:32.729
(laughs):
That's it.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.464
All right.

07:34.488 --> 07:36.468
What is that yellow stick?

07:37.491 --> 07:39.302
Oh, this is just a pencil.

07:39.326 --> 07:42.672
Uh, oh, it's what we use
to write with. What do you use?

07:42.696 --> 07:45.975
I use this. I can also use it
as a weapon to immobilize you.

07:45.999 --> 07:48.711
- Not now. (chuckles)
-(sighs)

07:48.735 --> 07:51.848
I can also point with it.
I can scratch with it.

07:51.872 --> 07:54.851
I can call people with it.
Hey, you, come here.

07:54.875 --> 07:57.253
Unique, isn't it?

07:57.277 --> 07:59.689
What is the purpose
of your visit to Earth?

07:59.713 --> 08:00.857
Purpose. Recall.

08:00.881 --> 08:02.258
(beeping, sputtering)

08:02.282 --> 08:04.761
Ah. I am here on your planet
to collect specimens

08:04.785 --> 08:06.596
for assembling on our planet.

08:06.620 --> 08:08.965
- No kidding?
-(speaks alien language)

08:08.989 --> 08:10.333
Anybody in particular?

08:10.357 --> 08:11.401
Yes.

08:11.425 --> 08:13.169
What, the president?!

08:13.193 --> 08:15.705
Oh, no, no, no,
not in Milwaukee. Uh...

08:15.729 --> 08:17.807
Are you gonna take Hank Aaron?

08:17.831 --> 08:20.410
Hank Aaron? (imitates bat
cracking, cheering) No, no.

08:20.434 --> 08:21.944
He is too famous.

08:21.968 --> 08:24.447
We would have to trade
the entire planet for him.

08:24.471 --> 08:27.550
- Oh. -What we need
is someone average.

08:27.574 --> 08:29.053
Humdrum.

08:36.783 --> 08:38.784
I know somebody humdrum.

08:45.759 --> 08:48.838
<i>RICHIE:
No, no, I-I can't go.</i>

08:48.862 --> 08:50.940
<i>I... Well, I can't
just leave like that.</i>

08:50.964 --> 08:52.341
Oh, it will
only take an instant.

08:52.365 --> 08:53.443
I'll bring you right back.

08:53.467 --> 08:54.710
Just an instant?

08:54.734 --> 08:56.079
(beeps)

08:56.103 --> 08:58.014
-I-I'll be back, just like that?
-(snaps fingers)

08:58.038 --> 09:00.450
Zabadee.

09:00.474 --> 09:03.920
- Just a zabadee?
-(speaks alien language)

09:03.944 --> 09:06.322
All right.
All right, what could it hurt?

09:06.346 --> 09:07.857
- I'm gonna go. I...
- Ah.

09:07.881 --> 09:09.792
All right, I-l got
to get some clothes.

09:09.816 --> 09:11.828
Uh, what do the men wear on Ork?

09:11.852 --> 09:14.097
Uh, same thing
our females do. Nothing.

09:14.121 --> 09:15.965
Females wear nothing?

09:15.989 --> 09:17.733
- Mm.
- What do they look like?

09:17.757 --> 09:19.302
- Ee-ee, ee-ee.
- Oh.

09:19.326 --> 09:22.338
Would you like to see
a picture of me and my girl?

09:22.362 --> 09:23.606
Yeah. Sure.

09:23.630 --> 09:25.234
Deebee.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.245
Oh, uh... which one is you?

09:29.269 --> 09:30.613
- Can't you tell?
- No.

09:30.637 --> 09:32.882
- That's why we don't bother
with clothes. -Oh.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.184
All right, uh... no clothes.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.587
So, I got to get a camera,
all right?

09:37.611 --> 09:39.021
And, uh, some film.

09:39.045 --> 09:41.124
I need more paper
and some pencils.

09:41.148 --> 09:43.259
See, I can't do that
with my finger the way you can.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.261
- Pity.
- Yeah.

09:45.285 --> 09:47.230
Would you mind if I just went
to my room and got that stuff?

09:47.254 --> 09:49.132
-(speaking alien language)
- Oh, fine. Thanks a lot.

09:49.156 --> 09:51.701
Oh, uh, listen,
just make yourself comfortable.

09:51.725 --> 09:53.069
You got the TV there.

09:53.093 --> 09:54.437
Oh, well, you broke that.

09:54.461 --> 09:55.838
No. Can repair instantly.

09:55.862 --> 09:57.273
(beep, music plays on TV)

09:57.297 --> 09:58.608
- Oh, very good!
-(speaks alien language)

09:58.632 --> 09:59.876
All right, and you got some food
there, too, all right?

09:59.900 --> 10:03.712
Food? Ah, fidba. Yay.

10:04.671 --> 10:06.015
(muttering)

10:06.039 --> 10:08.076
Needs salt.

10:12.279 --> 10:14.891
MAN (over TV): We return
to The Andy Griffith Show

10:14.915 --> 10:17.360
after these messages.

10:17.384 --> 10:20.092
I like that boy, Opie.

10:28.228 --> 10:30.806
Why does an Earth boy have
a Martian name, though?

10:30.830 --> 10:32.441
(indistinct voices on TV)

10:32.465 --> 10:34.610
- Well, I didn't like it.
- I liked it. I liked it.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.705
- No, I didn't like it.
- Well, it was so-so.

10:39.506 --> 10:41.508
It wasn't worth
the full price ticket.

10:43.043 --> 10:45.655
MARION:
Oh, my.

10:45.679 --> 10:48.191
Well, hello. Uh, you must be
a friend of Richard's.

10:48.215 --> 10:49.659
(grunts softly)

10:49.683 --> 10:51.661
Oh, I'm Howard Cunningham,
Richard's father,

10:51.685 --> 10:54.564
and this is Mrs. Cunningham
and our daughter Joanie.

10:54.588 --> 10:56.033
- JOANIE: Hi.
- I am Mork from Ork.

10:58.058 --> 11:00.334
Oh, thank you.

11:01.361 --> 11:03.773
Oh, I... Yes, O-R-K.

11:03.797 --> 11:05.441
- MORK: O-R-K.
- Yes.

11:05.465 --> 11:06.976
Well, Richard pledged A.T.0.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.678
He didn't have a suit like that.

11:08.702 --> 11:11.247
- MORK: Oh.
- No. They stuck feathers on him.

11:11.271 --> 11:14.081
I like feathers,
but I find them fattening.

11:16.142 --> 11:17.450
Oh, brother.

11:18.878 --> 11:22.091
He's another Ralph Malph.

11:22.115 --> 11:23.759
Uh, won't you make yourself
comfortable?

11:23.783 --> 11:25.785
Oh, thank you.

11:29.723 --> 11:33.402
Uh, well, I think
I'll just turn off the TV set.

11:33.426 --> 11:34.837
(high-pitched beeping)

11:36.763 --> 11:39.875
Jiminy Crickets,
there goes the TV again!

11:39.899 --> 11:41.244
Oh, dear.

11:41.268 --> 11:43.279
Uh, would you like something
to drink?

11:43.303 --> 11:45.081
Do you have any Pingee?

11:45.105 --> 11:47.183
MARION:
Pingee?

11:47.207 --> 11:49.018
It is a soft drink on Ork.

11:49.042 --> 11:50.386
Comes in five delicious flavors:

11:50.410 --> 11:53.789
Taz, Mah, Sheezba, Baba
and Shishwannee.

11:53.813 --> 11:57.159
Well, Mom, why don't you get
a case of Shishwannee?

11:57.183 --> 11:58.894
No, dear, it gives you cavities.

11:58.918 --> 11:59.895
Cavities.

11:59.919 --> 12:01.330
(loudly):
Ah, ah, ah, ah!

12:01.354 --> 12:03.356
(stifled grunting)

12:08.061 --> 12:10.573
I don't believe
what I'm hearing.

12:10.597 --> 12:14.110
(loudly): Richard, will you come
down here right away, please?

12:14.134 --> 12:16.045
Oh, Dad.

12:16.069 --> 12:17.847
Oh, Mom, good,
I'm glad you're here.

12:17.871 --> 12:20.549
Oh, a lot has happened
since the last time I saw you.

12:20.573 --> 12:22.518
I mean, I... well, I don't even
know where to start.

12:22.542 --> 12:23.986
I know where to start.

12:24.010 --> 12:25.388
You'll start with him.
Where did you find him?

12:25.412 --> 12:26.889
- Yeah, where did he come from?
-(overlapping chatter)

12:26.913 --> 12:28.357
What kind of man
did you bring in...?

12:28.381 --> 12:29.759
(high-pitched):
Boop...!

12:29.783 --> 12:30.793
Why did you do that?

12:30.817 --> 12:32.296
He drew first.

12:37.791 --> 12:39.769
Well, are they gonna be
all right?

12:39.793 --> 12:41.203
The effects wear off very soon.

12:41.227 --> 12:42.471
(low humming)

12:42.495 --> 12:44.540
Now we must hurry.
We do not have much time.

12:44.564 --> 12:47.109
All right. Okay, I just want
to make some, uh, sandwiches

12:47.133 --> 12:48.377
for the trip, okay?

12:48.401 --> 12:51.914
Do you have some of that
Earth delicacy, baloney?

12:51.938 --> 12:54.183
Uh, baloney? Well,
I-I'm not sure, but I'll check.

12:54.207 --> 12:56.744
We need it for fuel.

12:59.112 --> 13:01.090
Uh, how long are
we gonna be gone, anyway?

13:01.114 --> 13:02.658
Uh, about a bleem.

13:02.682 --> 13:03.926
Uh, a-a bleem.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.661
Okay, well how long
would that be in Earth time?

13:05.685 --> 13:07.196
- You know, a day, a week...
- Uh, Earth time.

13:07.220 --> 13:08.197
(electric beeping)

13:08.221 --> 13:09.962
2,000 years.

13:22.836 --> 13:24.647
Stop, Earth specimen.

13:24.671 --> 13:27.717
-(high-pitched): Eep!
-(pulsing)

13:27.741 --> 13:31.420
Shazbot, I missed.

13:31.444 --> 13:33.289
No one has ever
escaped from Mork.

13:33.313 --> 13:34.357
Think humdrum.

13:34.381 --> 13:36.492
Humdrum, humdrum, humdrum.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.086
(pulsing)

13:40.620 --> 13:43.065
<i>RICHIE: Fonz, I got to talk
to you; it's life and death.</i>

13:43.089 --> 13:44.166
What's up?

13:44.190 --> 13:45.835
Fonz, a guy's after me.

13:45.859 --> 13:47.532
Mork from Ork.

13:48.862 --> 13:51.507
I don't know him;
must be from the east side.

13:51.531 --> 13:52.775
No, no, no east side.

13:52.799 --> 13:54.009
I mean this is, uh,

13:54.033 --> 13:56.178
north through the Milky Way
and hang a right.

